In a message dated 12/24/02 4:31:01 PM Central Standard Time, 
wingedwarrior41@... writes:


&gt; Melchana stared at her astonished.
&gt; 
&gt; Melchana: You&#39;re a Decepticon?!? A techno-organic Decepticon?!? That
&gt; is... special to say the least.

&quot;This form is not of my own free will, mind you. I would prefer to regain my 
old form. But that fool, Alpha Trion stands in my way. No matter, I WILL 
regain my old form.&quot;

&gt; 
&gt; A signal came on her communicator.
&gt; 
&gt; Melchana: Clear. You can come. I made contact and am finding things out.
&gt; 
&gt; First, a monkey-looking bot came down. Seconds later, a huge bot
&gt; leaped and landed near there. He came closer and bowed his head.

She whipped her head about in the feline fear. But, soon that feline fear was 
disipating. Her real personality was starting to kick in. Effects,s he 
assumed, from the form change. 

&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan: Hi. I&#39;m Belthassan, leader of the Tripredacus Prophets.
&gt; Welcome to the New Cybertron!

She watched Belthassan with her icy optics. The words to her meant nothing. 
Except.. &quot;New Cybertron?&quot; She said slowly. 

&gt; 
&gt; Melchana: Bel, she&#39;s a Decepticon. She did mention Vector Sigma. You
&gt; think that...?
&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan looked at the feline transformer for a moment.
&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan: Possibly... Please, tell us more about you. Who were you
&gt; before?
&gt; 
&gt; 

She cocked a brow, something she never did before. &quot;I am Maxima, a Decepticon 
warrior. I was first created over 10 million years ago, aide to the 
Decepticon Dignitary Gemma Quadrun. I serve under Megatron, Leader of the 
Decepticons.&quot; 

She stood upon her paws & moved from the shadows to reveal the techno-organic 
form of a white tiger. She was understanding her form better. Cringing a 
moment then finally transformed into a humanoid form. 

&quot;Now, I have said too much. Tell me... what is Tripredacus? Please, do inform 
me as to what just happened & current events. As well... as help restore me 
to my original form.&quot; She grinned wickedly. 

